<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Assessment MathML 2.4//EN" "http://oli.web.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_assessment_mathml_2_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="_u9_cardio_introduction_quiz" recommended_attempts="1" max_attempts="6"><title>Cardiovascular System Introduction</title><page id="fd7b5db2a6764bbbbb6956896139e028"><multiple_choice id="_u9_cardioQuiz_01" grading="automatic" select="single"><body><p id="ae13af586fe22471c823c5e576203d007">The main function of the cardiovascular system is:</p></body><input shuffle="true" id="fd6ba6455a4242feb1cb34f1294ff3f0" labels="false"><choice value="A">absorb nutrients</choice><choice value="B">acquire oxygen</choice><choice value="C">moving material</choice><choice value="D">excreting waste</choice></input><part id="_u9_cardioQuiz_01_p1"><skillref idref="describe_major_functions_cardio_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="0"><feedback><p id="aefb179b6fb144d2690c956527ceb332a">Incorrect. The digestive system is responsible for absorbing nutrients.</p></feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback><p id="aeb20edd197a7417c8762b96d75e2294c">Incorrect. The respiratory system is responsible for acquiring oxygen.</p></feedback></response><response match="C" score="10"><feedback><p id="aa76939f4dd284e49b0c7ab2e1812053b">Correct. The cardiovascular system is responsible for moving materials.</p></feedback></response><response match="D" score="0"><feedback><p id="abae5e15c3202499ab2f62c965a75bc7a">Incorrect. Excretion of waste occurs from several systems, but not the cardiovascular system. </p></feedback></response></part></multiple_choice><multiple_choice id="_u9_cardioQuiz_02" grading="automatic" select="single"><body><p id="aaa09b6334fe7402b9cb240c96aaee033">Which of the following is not a cause of blood disorders?</p></body><input shuffle="false" id="b8c4ea1eed9843ababb7b306d417d944" labels="false"><choice value="A">environmental changes</choice><choice value="B">genetics</choice><choice value="C">pathogens</choice><choice value="D">All of these can cause blood disorders.</choice></input><part id="_u9_cardioQuiz_02_p1"><skillref idref="identify_major_diseases_cardio_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="0"><feedback><p id="aac8bec147cd54a7e8a3d4613c5fc9fd4">Incorrect. Environmental changes such as lack of nutrition can cause disorders.</p></feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback><p id="aee4a2904f0fb4209bbf5daf6f10d71aa">Incorrect. Genetics such as the sickle cell allele can cause blood disorders.</p></feedback></response><response match="C" score="0"><feedback><p id="ab52d995aa98a4fe0bfdf0f9076c37cc6">Incorrect. Pathogens such as a malaria infection can cause blood disorders.</p></feedback></response><response match="D" score="10"><feedback><p id="afac6a9433906432a915de7d9262b8479">Correct. All three of these things individually and together can result in a blood disorder. </p></feedback></response></part></multiple_choice></page></assessment>
